Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
read_metric(25.10)                                          read_metric(25.10)

Name
       read_metric  -  Loads  a previously saved metric file for querying, re-
       porting, and comparing

Syntax
        read_metric

       [-help]

       [-id <snapshotName>]

       <metricsFile>

       [-merge]

       [-previous <UniqueID>]

       Loads a previously saved metric file for querying, reporting, and  com-
       paring.

       The read_metric command allows you to manually load previous saved met-
       rics  files  into  an Innovus session. You can load any number of these
       files. However, these files should have a unique id.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each read_metric parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man read_metric

       -id< snapshotName >
              Specifies the name of snapshot to create or overwrite.

              Data_type: string, optional

       <metricsFile>
              Specifies the name of the metrics file.

              Data_type: string, required

       -merge Merges  the  metrics into the named snapshot, instead of replac-
              ing.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -previous <UniqueID>
              Specifies the uuid of previous snapshots  for  the  new  pending
              snapshot.

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
       The  following  code  shows  the usage of the read_metric command along
       with the write_metric command:

       # --------------------------------------------------------------------

       # Generate a XML file for all timing, power, and flow metrics from

       # from prects to postcts for a previous run (id v101)

       # --------------------------------------------------------------------

       read_metric -id v101 run101/dbs/postcts.enc.dat/design.metrics

       write_metric -id v101 -format xml -labels prects-postcts v101.xml

